[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":300},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F27\u002Fnodejs-nodemon-auto-restart\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F27\u002Fnodejs-nodemon-auto-restart\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F27\u002Fnodejs-nodemon-auto-restart\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F27\u002Fnodejs-nodemon-auto-restart\u002F":275,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F27\u002Fnodejs-nodemon-auto-restart\u002F":284},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20190627\u002F3580804465\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":257,"date":258,"description":259,"extension":260,"lang":261,"meta":262,"navigation":263,"path":264,"readingMinutes":265,"seo":266,"standalone":267,"stem":268,"tags":269,"tldr":272,"updated":272,"url":273,"__hash__":274},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fnodejs-nodemon-auto-restart.md","Node.js Basics, Part 6: Auto-Restarting Your App with nodemon","4658080345",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":247},"minimark",[11,16,33,37,40,50,53,58,83,87,107,119,123,129,136,143,149,172,175,180,187,193,200,215,221,225,243],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24,25,28,29,32],"p",{},"In the past, every time we changed a ",[21,22,23],"code",{},".js"," file, we had to stop and re-run ",[21,26,27],{},"node all.js",". That gets old fast, so let me introduce a really handy tool: ",[21,30,31],{},"nodemon",".",[12,34,36],{"id":35},"getting-started","Getting started",[17,38,39],{},"First we need to install the package. There are two ways to do it:",[41,42,43,47],"ol",{},[44,45,46],"li",{},"Install it globally on your machine",[44,48,49],{},"Install it in your project",[17,51,52],{},"The install commands are slightly different.",[54,55,57],"h3",{"id":56},"installing-globally","Installing globally",[59,60,65],"pre",{"className":61,"code":62,"language":63,"meta":64,"style":64},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","npm install nodemon -g\n","js","",[21,66,67],{"__ignoreMap":64},[68,69,72,76,80],"span",{"class":70,"line":71},"line",1,[68,73,75],{"class":74},"sMAXC","npm install nodemon ",[68,77,79],{"class":78},"sWyjQ","-",[68,81,82],{"class":74},"g\n",[54,84,86],{"id":85},"installing-in-your-project","Installing in your project",[59,88,90],{"className":61,"code":89,"language":63,"meta":64,"style":64},"npm install nodemon --save-dev\n",[21,91,92],{"__ignoreMap":64},[68,93,94,96,99,102,104],{"class":70,"line":71},[68,95,75],{"class":74},[68,97,98],{"class":78},"--",[68,100,101],{"class":74},"save",[68,103,79],{"class":78},[68,105,106],{"class":74},"dev\n",[108,109,110],"blockquote",{},[17,111,112,116,118],{},[113,114,115],"strong",{},"Note",[21,117,31],{}," is only used during development, so you don't need it in production — just the dev environment.",[54,120,122],{"id":121},"how-to-use-it","How to use it",[17,124,125,126,32],{},"Once it's installed, you can check the version with ",[21,127,128],{},"nodemon -v",[17,130,131],{},[132,133],"img",{"alt":134,"src":135},"nodemon version","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQWCLMAC.png",[108,137,138],{},[17,139,140,142],{},[113,141,115],{},"\nI installed it globally, so I can run it from anywhere.",[17,144,145,146,148],{},"Using it is dead simple. Say the ",[21,147,23],{}," file you want to run is on your desktop — you'd just write:",[59,150,152],{"className":61,"code":151,"language":63,"meta":64,"style":64},"cd C:\\Users\\Hsiangfeng\\Desktop\\project\nnodemon all.js\n",[21,153,154,166],{"__ignoreMap":64},[68,155,156,159,163],{"class":70,"line":71},[68,157,158],{"class":74},"cd ",[68,160,162],{"class":161},"s_sBn","C",[68,164,165],{"class":74},":\\Users\\Hsiangfeng\\Desktop\\project\n",[68,167,169],{"class":70,"line":168},2,[68,170,171],{"class":74},"nodemon all.js\n",[17,173,174],{},"After running it, you'll see this:",[17,176,177],{},[132,178],{"alt":31,"src":179},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FtqnKFtq.png",[17,181,182,183,186],{},"From now on, whenever you change ",[21,184,185],{},"all.js",", it'll restart automatically.",[17,188,189],{},[132,190],{"alt":191,"src":192},"auto reset","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FkWpDeS3.png",[17,194,195,196,199],{},"One last gotcha: if you don't ",[21,197,198],{},"cd"," into the project directory first and instead run the command like this:",[59,201,203],{"className":61,"code":202,"language":63,"meta":64,"style":64},"nodemon C:\\Users\\Hsiangfeng\\Desktop\\project\\all.js\n",[21,204,205],{"__ignoreMap":64},[68,206,207,210,212],{"class":70,"line":71},[68,208,209],{"class":74},"nodemon ",[68,211,162],{"class":161},[68,213,214],{"class":74},":\\Users\\Hsiangfeng\\Desktop\\project\\all.js\n",[17,216,217,218,32],{},"you might run into a problem where it ",[113,219,220],{},"won't auto-restart",[12,222,224],{"id":223},"one-more-thing","One more thing",[17,226,227,228,230,231,234,235,242],{},"Again, ",[21,229,31],{}," is only for development mode — in production you'd just use ",[21,232,233],{},"node",". For the reasoning behind that, ",[236,237,241],"a",{"href":238,"rel":239},"https:\u002F\u002Fmedium.com\u002F@will.wang\u002Fnodejs-and-nodemon-blackhole-2651c7f8307e",[240],"nofollow","this article"," is worth a read.",[244,245,246],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}",{"title":64,"searchDepth":168,